s.", "Wait_next");\n        if (stats1.errors_done) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "done", stats1.errors_done, stats1.errortime_done);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "done");\n        if (stats1.errors_counting) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "counting", stats1.errors_counting, stats1.errortime_counting);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "counting");\n        if (stats1.errors_shift_ena) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "shift_ena", stats1.errors_shift_ena, stats1.errortime_shift_ena);\n        else $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "shift_ena");\n\n        $display("Hint: Total mismatched samples is %1d out of %1d samples\\n", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n        $display("Simulation finished at %0d ps", $time);\n        $display("Mismatches: %1d in %1d samples", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n    end\n    \n    initial begin\n      #1000000\n      $display("TIMEOUT");\n      $finish();\n    end\n\nendmodule\n</testbench>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe module interface is given below:\n<module_interface>\nmodule TopModule (\n    input  logic        d,\n    input  logic        done_counting,\n    input  logic        ack,\n    input  logic [9:0]  state,\n    output logic        B3_next,\n    output logic        S_next,\n    output logic        S1_next,\n    output logic        Count_next,\n    output logic        Wait_next,\n    output logic        done,\n    output logic        counting,\n    output logic        shift_ena\n);\nendmodule\n</module_interface>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "1. **Analyze State Encoding**: The specification requires one-hot encoding for the 10 states. Let\'s map the states to their bit positions in the 10-bit `state` signal:\\n   - S: 10\'b0000000001 (bit 0)\\n   - S1: 10\'b0000000010 (bit 1)\\n   - S11: 10\'b0000000100 (bit 2)\\n   - S110: 10\'b0000001000 (bit 3)\\n   - B0: 10\'b0000010000 (bit 4)\\n   - B1: 10\'b0000100000 (bit 5)\\n   - B2: 10\'b0001000000 (bit 6)\\n   - B3: 10\'b0010000000 (bit 7)\\n   - Count: 10\'b0100000000 (bit 8)\\n   - Wait: 10\'b1000000000 (bit 9)\\n\\n2. **Determine Next-State Logic**: \\n   - `S_next`: S (d=0) or Wait (ack=1). Logic: `state[0] & ~d | state[9] & ack`.\\n   - `S1_next`: S (d=1). Logic: `state[0] & d`.\\n   - `S11_next`: S1 (d=1) or S11 (d=1). Logic: `state[1] & d | state[2] & d`.\\n   - `S110_next`: S11 (d=0). Logic: `state[2] & ~d`.\\n   - `B0_next`: S110 (d=1). Logic: `state[3] & d`.\\n   - `B1_next`: B0. Logic: `state[4]`.\\n   - `B2_next`: B1. Logic: `state[5]`.\\n   - `B3_next`: B2. Logic: `state[6]`.\\n   - `Count_next`: B3. Logic: `state[7]`.\\n   - `Wait_next`: Count (done_counting=1). Logic: `state[8] & done_counting`.\\n   - `Wait_next` (re-check): Count (done_counting=1) -> Wait. Correct.\\n   - Wait (re-check): Count (done_counting=0) -> Count. Wait, the spec says `Count (counting=1) --done_counting=0--> Count`. So Count stays Count if `done_counting=0`.\\n   - Wait (re-check): Wait (ack=0) -> Wait. So Wait stays Wait if `ack=0`.\\n   - `Count_next` (refinement): `state[8] & ~done_counting | state[9] & ~ack`? No, wait. Let\'s look at the state machine transitions again.\\n   \\n   Transitions:\\n   S -> S (d=0), S1 (d=1)\\n   S1 -> S (d=0), S11 (d=1)\\n   S11 -> S11 (d=1), S110 (d=0)\\n   S110 -> B0 (d=1), S (d=0)\\n   B0 -> B1\\n   B1 -> B2\\n   B2 -> B3\\n   B3 -> Count\\n   Count -> Count (done_counting=0), Wait (done_counting=1)\\n   Wait -> Wait (ack=0), S (ack=1)\\n\\n   Next-State Signals:\\n   - `S_next`: `state[0] & ~d | state[1] & ~d | state[3] & ~d | state[9] & ack`\\n   - `S1_next`: `state[0] & d`\\n   - `S11_next`: `state[1] & d | state[2] & d`\\n   - `S110_next`: `state[2] & ~d`\\n   - `B0_next`: `state[3] & d`\\n   - `B1_next`: `state[4]`\\n   - `B2_next`: `state[5]`\\n   - `B3_next`: `state[6]`\\n   - `Count_next`: `state[7] | (state[8] & ~done_counting)`\\n   - `Wait_next`: `state[8] & done_counting | state[9] & ~ack`\\n\\n3. **Determine Output Logic**:\\n   - `done`: Output of Wait state. Logic: `state[9]`.\\n   - `counting`: Output of Count state. Logic: `state[8]`.\\n   - `shift_ena`: Output of B0, B1, B2, B3 states. Logic: `state[4] | state[5] | state[6] | state[7]`.\\n\\n4. **Advice to avoid syntax errors**:\\n   - Always use `always @(*)` for combinational logic to avoid sensitivity list issues.\\n   - Ensure all bits of the 10-bit state are addressed correctly via index `state[i]`.\\n   - Match the port names exactly as specified in the interface.\\n   - Use `logic` for all signal declarations.",\n    "module": "module TopModule (\\n    input  logic        d,\\n    input  logic        done_counting,\\n    input  logic        ack,\\n    input  logic [9:0]  state,\\n    output logic        B3_next,\\n    output logic        S_next,\\n    output logic        S1_next,\\n    output logic        Count_next,\\n    output logic        Wait_next,\\n    output logic        done,\\n    output logic        counting,\\n    output logic        shift_ena\\n);\\n\\n    // Next state indicators\\n    // S: bit 0, S1: bit 1, S11: bit 2, S110: bit 3, B0: bit 4, B1: bit 5, B2: bit 6, B3: bit 7, Count: bit 8, Wait: bit 9\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Default values for next state signals\\n        S_next      = 1\'b0;\\n        S1_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        S11_next    = 1\'b0; // Intermediate for logic\\n        S110_next   = 1\'b0; // Intermediate for logic\\n        B0_next     = 1\'b0; // Intermediate for logic\\n        B1_next     = 1\'b0; // Intermediate for logic\\n        B2_next     = 1\'b0; // Intermediate for logic\\n        B3_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        Count_next  = 1\'b0;\\n        Wait_next   = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        // S transitions\\n        if (state[0]) begin\\n            if (d) S1_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else    S_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n\\n        // S1 transitions\\n        if (state[1]) begin\\n            if (d) S1_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else    S_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n\\n        // S11 transitions\\n        if (state[2]) begin\\n            if (d) S1_next = 1\'b1; // Spec says S11 --d=1--> S11. Wait, let me re-read.\\n            // Spec: S11 --d=1--> S11. S11 --d=0--> S110.\\n            // Re-evaluating S11 logic based on spec\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Let\'s rewrite the logic more cleanly based on the exact spec provided\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Initialize all next-state outputs\\n        S_next      = 1\'b0;\\n        S1_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        B3_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        Count_next  = 1\'b0;\\n        Wait_next   = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        // Transition Logic from spec\\n        // S --d=0--> S\\n        // S --d=1--> S1\\n        if (state[0]) begin\\n            if (!d) S_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else     S1_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n\\n        // S1 --d=0--> S\\n        // S1 --d=1--> S11\\n        if (state[1]) begin\\n            if (!d) S_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else     S1_next = 1\'b1; // wait, spec says S1 --d=1--> S11. S1_next is for S1 state.\\n            // Note: The requirement is to assert S1_next when next-state is S1 state.\\n            // So if current is S and d=1, next is S1, so S1_next = 1.\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Let\'s start over with a very precise implementation\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        S_next      = 1\'b0;\\n        S1_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        B3_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        Count_next  = 1\'b0;\\n        Wait_next   = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        // State transitions\\n        // S (0) -> S (0) if d=0, S1 (1) if d=1\\n        if (state[0]) begin\\n            if (!d) S_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else     S1_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // S1 (1) -> S (0) if d=0, S11 (2) if d=1\\n        else if (state[1]) begin\\n            if (!d) S_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else     /* next state is S11 */ ;\\n        end\\n        // S11 (2) -> S11 (2) if d=1, S110 (3) if d=0\\n        else if (state[2]) begin\\n            if (d) /* next state is S11 */ ;\\n            else   /* next state is S110 */ ;\\n        end\\n        // S110 (3) -> B0 (4) if d=1, S (0) if d=0\\n        else if (state[3]) begin\\n            if (d) /* next state is B0 */ ;\\n            else   S_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // B0 (4) -> B1 (5)\\n        else if (state[4]) begin\\n            /* next state is B1 */ ;\\n        end\\n        // B1 (5) -> B2 (6)\\n        else if (state[5]) begin\\n            /* next state is B2 */ ;\\n        end\\n        // B2 (6) -> B3 (7)\\n        else if (state[6]) begin\\n            B3_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // B3 (7) -> Count (8)\\n        else if (state[7]) begin\\n            Count_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // Count (8) -> Count (8) if done_counting=0, Wait (9) if done_counting=1\\n        else if (state[8]) begin\\n            if (!done_counting) Count_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else                 Wait_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // Wait (9) -> Wait (9) if ack=0, S (0) if ack=1\\n        else if (state[9]) begin\\n            if (!ack) Wait_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else      S_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Corrected logic based on exhaustive check of all transitions\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Reset all next-state flags\\n        S_next      = 1\'b0;\\n        S1_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        B3_next     = 1\'b0;\\n        Count_next  = 1\'b0;\\n        Wait_next   = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        // S (bit 0) transitions\\n        if (state[0]) begin\\n            if (!d) S_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else     S1_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // S1 (bit 1) transitions\\n        else if (state[1]) begin\\n            if (!d) S_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else     /* next state is S11 (bit 2) */ ;\\n        end\\n        // S11 (bit 2) transitions\\n        else if (state[2]) begin\\n            if (d)  /* next state is S11 (bit 2) */ ;\\n            else    /* next state is S110 (bit 3) */ ;\\n        end\\n        // S110 (bit 3) transitions\\n        else if (state[3]) begin\\n            if (d)  /* next state is B0 (bit 4) */ ;\\n            else    S_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // B0 (bit 4) transitions\\n        else if (state[4]) begin\\n            /* next state is B1 (bit 5) */ ;\\n        end\\n        // B1 (bit 5) transitions\\n        else if (state[5]) begin\\n            /* next state is B2 (bit 6) */ ;\\n        end\\n        // B2 (bit 6) transitions\\n        else if (state[6]) begin\\n            B3_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // B3 (bit 7) transitions\\n        else if (state[7]) begin\\n            Count_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // Count (bit 8) transitions\\n        else if (state[8]) begin\\n            if (!done_counting) Count_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else                 Wait_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n        // Wait (bit 9) transitions\\n        else if (state[9]) begin\\n            if (!ack) Wait_next = 1\'b1;\\n            else      S_next = 1\'b1;\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Wait, the logic above is still slightly fragmented. Let\'s do a direct implementation.\\n\\n    // Re-calculating based on the spec one-by-one:\\n    // S_next: (state[0] & ~d) | (state[1] & ~d) | (state[3] & ~d) | (state[9] & ack)\\n    // S1_next: (state[0] & d) | (state[1] & d) | (state[2] & d) [Wait, S11--d=1-->S11, S1--d=1-->S11, S--d=1-->S1]\\n    // Let\'s look at the transitions again.\\n    // S: d=0->S, d=1->S1\\n    // S1: d=0->S, d=1->S11\\n    // S11: d=0->S110, d=1->S11\\n    // S110: d=0->S, d=1->B0\\n    // B0: always B1\\n    // B1: always B2\\n    // B2: always B3\\n    // B3: always Count\\n    // Count: dc=0->Count, dc=1->Wait\\n    // Wait: ack=0->Wait, ack=1->S\\n\\n    // Final logic mapping:\\n    // S_next = (state[0] & ~d) | (state[1] & ~d) | (state[3] & ~d) | (state[9] & ack)\\n    // S1_next = (state[0] & d)\\n    // S11_next = (state[1] & d) | (state[2] & d)\\n    // S110_next = (state[2] & ~d)\\n    // B0_next = (state[3] & d)\\n    // B1_next = state[4]\\n    // B2_next = state[5]\\n    // B3_next = state[6]\\n    // Count_next = state[7] | (state[8] & ~done_counting)\\n    // Wait_next = (state[8] & done_counting) | (state[9] & ~ack)\\n\\n    // Wait, the module outputs requested are B3_next, S_next, S1_next, Count_next, Wait_next, done, counting, shift_ena.\\n\\n    // Let\'s verify the outputs:\\n    // done: output logic. Moore machine: output is based on current state. \\n    // Wait state (bit 9) outputs done=1.\\n    // counting: Count state (bit 8) outputs counting=1.\\n    // shift_ena: B0, B1, B2, B3 states output shift_ena=1. \\n    // That is bits 4, 5, 6, 7.\\n\\n    // Re-implementing with this exact logic:\\n\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        S_next = (state[0] & ~d) | (state[1] & ~d) | (state[3] & ~d) | (state[9] & ack);\\n        S1_next = (state[0] & d);\\n        B3_next = state[6];\\n        Count_next = state[7] | (state[8] & ~done_counting);\\n        Wait_next = (state[8] & done_counting) | (state[9] & ~ack);\\n    end\\n\\n    assign done = state[9];\\n    assign counting = state[8];\\n    assign shift_ena = state[4] | state[5] | state[6] | state[7];\\n\\nendmodule"\n}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe error below has been reported by the format tool:\n<format_error>\n{\n    "stdout": "",\n    "stderr": "./output_t22b_gemma4_26b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob150_review2015_fsmonehot/rtl.sv:23: error: Could not find variable ``S11_next\'\' in ``TopModule\'\'\\